<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-55-0217 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Ultrasonic Ranging and Data System (USRADS) was developed to allowradiation exposure data and positional information to be collected, storedand analyzed in a more efficient manner than currently employed on the(Uranium Mill Tailings Remedial Action (UMTRA) project. USRADS is a portableunit which employs ultrasonics, radio frequency transmissions, and apersonal computer. Operational experience indicates that the system resultsin increased information about the property with decreased data analysisand transcription effort and only slightly more field effort. 5 refs.,3 figs., 2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>